The directors register more and more bookings.
It's a good winter for the German tour operators.
According to one study, the turnover of the road bookings for the coming months increased significantly compared to the previous year - by more than 30 percent for the winter season.
Despite the weak economic outlook, the Germans' travel mood has not diminished according to the study.
In winter season bookings, travel agencies recorded a 31 percent increase in turnover compared to the previous year, the German Travel Association (DRV) announced on Monday in Berlin.
